               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]]: 171 translates: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a1 Turn then! (i.e. Convert [him] then!) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 of the dharma cakravartin.hood &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 ... previously of all the best ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a4 ... with ... Trapusa and Bhallika ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a5 eightfold. He who, in the time to come [=saṅgha], &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a6 With insatiable gaze. The insatiable gaze of the teacher of the tribhuvana. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a7 The Sumeru mountain, you the giver of refuge we make with faith &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b1 The Buddha teacher speaks these ślokas to the merchants with [his] loving spirit. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 This immortal one. The god Māra and so on who strive after evil for him. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b3 Having worshipped his feet with faith [they are converted]. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 Having annihilated all the crimes ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b5 He who, having eaten alms, &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b6 From [his] throne he destroys ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b7 The ... of the three asaṃkhyeyas &lt;/p&gt;</item>
